<i>On the path unwinding</i>

55
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:27,475
<i>In the circle</i>

56
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:33,940
<i>The circle of life</i>

57
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:58,506
Life's not fair, is it?

58
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:02,969
You see, I... Well, I shall never be king.

59
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:08,391
And you shall never see
the light of another day.

60
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:10,685
Adieu.

61
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:14,480
Didn't your mother ever tell you
not to play with your food?

62
00:05:15,022 --> 00:05:16,357
What do you want?

63
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:19,861
I'm here to announce that
King Mufasa's on his way,

64
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:23,531
so you'd better have a good excuse
for missing this morning's ceremony.

65
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:25,199
Oh, look, Zazu.

66
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:26,534
You've made me lose my lunch.

67
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:29,537
You'll lose more than that
when the king gets through with you.

68
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:32,290
He's as mad as a hippo with a hernia.

69
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:35,877
I quiver with fear!

70
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:38,462
Now, Scar, don't look at me that way.

71
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:39,881
Help!

72
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:42,133
- Scar?
- Mm-hmm?

73
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:43,384
Drop him.

74
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:46,721
Impeccable timing, Your Majesty.

75
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:53,936
Why, if it isn't my big brother
descending from on high

76
00:05:54,061 --> 00:05:56,063
to mingle with the commoners.

77
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:59,275
Sarabi and I didn't see you
at the presentation of Simba.

78
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,485
That was today?

79
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,905
I feel simply awful!

80
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:05,072
(SCREECHING)

81
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:07,909
Must've slipped my mind.

82
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:11,162
Yes, well, as slippery as your mind is,

83
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:14,165
as the king's brother,
you should've been first in line!

84
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:19,253
Well, I was first in line,
until the little hairball was born.

85
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:24,300
That hairball is my son
and your future king.

86
00:06:24,425 --> 00:06:27,094
I shall practice my curtsy!

87
00:06:27,428 --> 00:06:29,764
Don't turn your back on me, Scar.

88
00:06:29,805 --> 00:06:31,140
Oh, no, Mufasa.

89
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:34,101
Perhaps you shouldn't
turn your back on me.

90
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:35,269
(ROARS)

91
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:37,104
Is that a challenge?

92
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:38,648
Temper, temper.

93
00:06:39,106 --> 00:06:41,943
I wouldn't dream of challenging you.

94
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,945
Pity. Why not?

95
00:06:43,986 --> 00:06:47,323
Well, as far as brains go,
I got the lion's share.

96
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:50,785
But when it comes to brute strength,

97
00:06:50,826 --> 00:06:54,997
I'm afraid I'm at the shallow end
of the gene pool.

98
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,378
There's one in every family, sire.

99
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,004
Two in mine, actually,

100
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:05,216
and they always manage to
ruin special occasions.

101
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,301
What am I going to do with him?

102
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:09,136
He'd make a very handsome throw rug.

103
00:07:09,178 --> 00:07:10,304
Zazu!

104
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:12,807
And just think, whenever he gets dirty,

105
00:07:12,848 --> 00:07:14,976
you could take him out and beat him.

106
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:16,352
(CHUCKLES)

107
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:49,677
(MUTTERING)

108
00:07:54,849 --> 00:07:56,017
Hmm.

109
00:08:00,521 --> 00:08:02,189
Simba.

110
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,525
(CHUCKLES)

111
00:08:15,786 --> 00:08:17,038
Dad! Dad!

112
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:19,540
Come on, dad, we gotta go! Wake up!

113
00:08:20,207 --> 00:08:21,876
- Uhh!
- Sorry.

114
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:25,296
- (SNORING)
- Dad! Dad!

115
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:28,257
Your son is awake.

116
00:08:28,382 --> 00:08:31,385
Before sunrise, he's your son.

117
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:33,596
Dad! Come on, Dad.

118
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:40,061
You promised.

119
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:42,730
Okay, Okay. I'm up, I'm up.

120
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:43,898
Yeah!

121
00:09:00,247 --> 00:09:01,248
MUFASA: Look, Simba.

122
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:05,461
Everything the light
touches is our kingdom.

123
00:09:05,586 --> 00:09:07,254
Wow.

124
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:12,259
A king's time as ruler
rises and falls like the sun.

125
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:16,305
One day, Simba,
the sun will set on my time here

126
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:19,809
and will rise with you as the new king.

127
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:22,603
- And this'll all be mine?
- Everything.

128
00:09:22,686 --> 00:09:25,606
Everything the light touches.

129
00:09:26,273 --> 00:09:27,817
What about that shadowy place?

130
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,027
That's beyond our borders.

131
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:31,487
You must never go there, Simba.

132
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:33,656
But I thought a king
can do whatever he wants.

133
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:37,118
Oh, there's more to being king
than getting your way all the time.

134
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,495
- There's more?
- (LAUGHS) Simba...

135
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:47,670
Everything you see exists together
in a delicate balance.

136
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:50,673
As king, you need to
understand that balance

137
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,508
and respect all the creatures,

138
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,469
from the crawling ant
to the leaping antelope.

139
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:57,346
But, Dad, don't we eat the antelope?

140
00:09:57,471 --> 00:10:00,015
Yes, Simba, but let me explain.

141
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:03,060
When we die, our bodies
become the grass,

142
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,855
and the antelope eat the grass.

143
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:11,193
And so we are all connected
in the great circle of life.

144
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,529
- Good morning, sire!
- Good morning, Zazu.

145
00:10:13,612 --> 00:10:15,448
Checking in with the morning report.

146
00:10:15,531 --> 00:10:16,574
Fire away.

147
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:18,367
Well! The buzz from the bees

148
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:20,327
is that the leopards
are in a bit of a spot.

149
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:21,495
Really?

150
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:23,914
What are you doing, son?

151
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:25,541
Pouncing.

152
00:10:25,624 --> 00:10:27,960
Let an old pro show you how it's done.

153
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:31,005
I told the elephants to forget it,
but they can't...

154
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:32,882
- Zazu, would you turn around?
- Yes, sire.

155
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:34,109
The cheetahs are hard up, but...

156
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,801
Stay low to the ground.

157
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:37,219
Cheetahs never prosper...

158
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:39,406
(WHISPERING) Yeah, okay.
Stay low to the ground, right? Yeah.

159
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,699
- What going on?
- A pouncing lesson.

160
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:42,933
Very good. Pouncing.

161
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:46,437
Pouncing?
No, sire, you can't be serious...

162
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,231
This is so humiliating.

163
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,900
Try not to make a sound.

164
00:10:50,983 --> 00:10:53,235
What are you telling him, Mufasa?

165
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,572
Mufasa? Simba?

166
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,992
(MUFASA LAUGHS)

167
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:01,660
That's very good.

168
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,579
- Zazu!
- Yes!

169
00:11:03,662 --> 00:11:06,290
- News from the underground.
- Now, this time...

170
00:11:06,373 --> 00:11:09,668
Sire! Hyenas in the Pride Lands!

171
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,253
Zazu, take Simba home.

172
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,463
Aw, dad, can't I come?

173
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:13,672
No, son.

174
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:16,926
Pah! I never get to go anywhere.

175
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:21,096
Oh, young master,
one day, you will be king.

176
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:25,059
Then you can chase those
slobbering, mangy, stupid poachers

177
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:27,186
from dawn until dusk.

178
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:36,612
Hey, Uncle Scar! Guess what?

179
00:11:36,695 --> 00:11:39,782
I despise guessing games.

180
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:41,951
I'm gonna be King of Pride Rock.

181
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:44,245
Oh, goody!

182
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:46,121
My dad just showed me
the whole kingdom,

183
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:49,208
and I'm gonna rule it all!

184
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:52,795
Yes. Well, forgive me
for not leaping for joy.

185
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:55,172
Bad back, you know.

186
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,341
Hey, Uncle Scar.

187
00:11:57,424 --> 00:11:59,802
When I'm king, what'll that make you?

188
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,137
A monkey's uncle.

189
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:06,016
- You're so weird.
- You have no idea.

190
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:09,311
So, your father showed you
the whole kingdom, did he?

191
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,437
Everything.

192
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:14,108
He didn't show you what's beyond
that rise at the northern border?

193
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:17,653
Well, no. He said I can't go there.

194
00:12:17,736 --> 00:12:19,738
And he's absolutely right.

195
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:21,156
It's far too dangerous.

196
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,659
Only the bravest lions go there.

197
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:26,412
Well, I'm brave. What's out there?

198
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:28,872
I'm sorry, Simba, I just can't tell you.

199
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:30,040
Why not?

200
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:34,545
I'm only looking out for the
well-being of my favorite nephew.

201
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:37,506
Yeah, right! I'm your only nephew.

202
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:40,092
All the more reason
for me to be protective.

203
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:44,388
An elephant graveyard is no place
for a young prince. Oops!

204
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,099
An elephant what? Whoa!

205
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:50,311
Oh, dear, I've said too much.

206
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:53,230
Well, I suppose you'd have
found out sooner or later,

207
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:56,317
you being so clever and all.

208
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,110
Just do me one favor.

209
00:12:58,193 --> 00:13:02,781
Promise me you'll never visit
that dreadful place.

210
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:04,283
No problem.

211
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,993
There's a good lad.

212
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:08,829
You run along now and have fun.

213
00:13:08,912 --> 00:13:10,414
And remember,

214
00:13:10,497 --> 00:13:13,000
it's our little secret.

215
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,134
- Hey, Nala.
- Hi, Simba.

216
00:13:22,217 --> 00:13:24,345
Come on. I just heard
about this great place.

217
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:26,972
Simba! I'm kind of
in the middle of a bath.

218
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,099
SARABI: And it's time for yours.

219
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:32,227
Mom!

220
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:35,189
Mom, you're messing up my mane!

221
00:13:36,523 --> 00:13:39,068
Okay, okay, I'm clean.
Can we go now?

222
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:40,444
So, where are we going?

223
00:13:40,527 --> 00:13:42,071
It better not be anyplace dumb.

224
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:43,989
No, it's really cool.

225
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:46,575
So, where is this really cool place?

226
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,077
Oh.

227
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,829
- Uh, around the water hole.
- The water hole?

228
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:52,706
What's so great about the water hole?

229
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,958
I'll show you when we get there.

230
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:56,210
Oh.

231
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:58,128
Uh, mom, can I go with Simba?

232
00:13:58,545 --> 00:14:00,464
Hmm, what do you think, Sarabi?

233
00:14:00,547 --> 00:14:01,590
Well...

234
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,092
BOTH: Please?

235
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:04,301
It's all right with me.

236
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:05,469
- Yeah!
- All right!

237
00:14:05,552 --> 00:14:07,471
As long as Zazu goes with you.

238
00:14:07,554 --> 00:14:09,139
No, not Zazu.

239
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:10,766
ZAZU: Step lively.

240
00:14:10,849 --> 00:14:14,812
The sooner we get to the water hole,
the sooner we can leave.

241
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,772
So, where are we really going?

242
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:18,232
An elephant graveyard.

243
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:19,358
Wow!

244
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:20,943
Shh! Zazu.

245
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:23,737
Right. So, how are we
gonna ditch the dodo?

246
00:14:24,571 --> 00:14:26,657
Oh, just look at you two.

247
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:29,868
Little seeds of romance
blossoming in the savanna.

248
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:32,162
Your parents will be thrilled,

249
00:14:32,287 --> 00:14:34,623
what with your being betrothed and all.

250
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:35,749
Be-what?

251
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,543
Betrothed. Intended.

252
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,545
Affianced.

253
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:40,671
Meaning...

254
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:43,757
One day, you two are
going to be married.

255
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:44,883
- Yuck!
- Eww!

256
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,177
I can't marry her. She's my friend.

257
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:49,471
Yeah, it'd be so weird.

258
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:51,473
Sorry to bust your bubble,

259
00:14:51,598 --> 00:14:54,184
but you two turtle doves
have no choice.

260
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,729
It's a tradition going back generations.

261
00:14:56,812 --> 00:14:59,356
When I'm king,
that'll be the first thing to go.

262
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:02,276
- Not so long as I'm around.
- Well, in that case, you're fired.

263
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,778
Nice try, but only the king can do that.

264
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:06,447
Well, he's the future king.

265
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,907
Yeah, so you have to do what I tell you.

266
00:15:09,032 --> 00:15:10,451
Not yet, I don't.

267
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:11,994
And with an attitude like that,

268
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:15,873
I'm afraid you're shaping up to be
a pretty pathetic king, indeed.

269
00:15:15,956 --> 00:15:17,541
Not the way I see it.

270
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,711
(SINGING) <i>I'm gonna be a mighty king</i>

271
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:22,880
<i>So enemies beware</i>

272
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:25,549
<i>Well, I've never seen
a king of beasts</i>

273
00:15:25,632 --> 00:15:27,801
<i>With quite so little hair</i>

274
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:30,512
<i>I'm gonna be the main event</i>

275
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:32,639
<i>Like no king was before</i>

276
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:35,350
<i>I'm brushin' up on lookin' down</i>

277
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,561
<i>I'm workin' on my roar</i>

278
00:15:37,644 --> 00:15:41,273
<i>Thus far, a rather uninspiring thing</i>

279
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:46,236
<i>Oh, I just can't wait to be king</i>

280
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:49,490
You've rather a long way to go,
young master, if you think...

281
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,909
<i>- No one sayin', "Do this"
- Now, when I said that...</i>

282
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:54,411
<i>- No one saying, "Be there"
- What I meant was...</i>

283
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,830
<i>- No one sayin', "Stop that"
- You don't realize...</i>

284
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:59,750
<i>- No one sayin', "See here"
- Now, see here!</i>

285
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:03,170
<i>Free to run around all day</i>

286
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:04,838
Well, that's definitely out.

287
00:16:04,922 --> 00:16:08,926
<i>Free to do it all my way</i>

288
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:14,264
<i>I think it's time that you and I</i>

289
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:16,391
<i>Arranged a heart-to-heart</i>

290
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:18,268
<i>Kings don't need advice</i>

291
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:20,896
<i>From little hornbills for a start</i>

292
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:24,483
<i>if this is where
the monarchy is headed</i>

293
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:25,734
<i>Count me out</i>

294
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:28,278
<i>Out of service, out of Africa</i>

295
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:30,906
<i>I wouldn't hang about</i>

296
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:35,327
<i>This child is getting
wildly out of wing</i>

297
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:39,873
<i>Oh, I just can't wait to be king</i>

298
00:16:52,427 --> 00:16:54,179
<i>Everybody, look left</i>

299
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:57,057
<i>Everybody, look right</i>

300
00:16:57,432 --> 00:16:59,643
<i>Everywhere you look, I'm</i>

301
00:16:59,726 --> 00:17:01,353
<i>Standing in the spotlight</i>

302
00:17:01,436 --> 00:17:03,146
Not yet!

303
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:06,984
<i>Let every creature
go for broke and sing</i>

304
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:10,946
<i>Let's hear it in the herd
and on the wing</i>

305
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:16,660
<i>It's gonna be
King Simba's finest fling</i>

306
00:17:16,743 --> 00:17:21,665
<i>Oh, I just can't wait to be king</i>

307
00:17:21,748 --> 00:17:26,587
<i>Oh, I just can't wait to be king</i>

308
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:31,508
<i>Oh, I just can't wait</i>

309
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:34,845
<i>To be king</i>

310
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:43,812
ZAZU: (MUFFLED)
I beg your pardon, madam, but

311
00:17:43,979 --> 00:17:45,898
get off!

312
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:47,566
Simba?

313
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:49,860
Nala!

314
00:17:51,194 --> 00:17:52,237
(LAUGHING)

315
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,655
All right! It worked!

316
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:56,241
- We lost him.
- I am a genius.

317
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:58,368
Hey, genius, it was my idea.

318
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:00,621
Yeah, but I pulled it off.

319
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:02,664
- With me!
- Oh, yeah?

320
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:08,962
- Pinned ya.
- Hey, let me up!

321
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,757
(LAUGHING)

322
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,844
Pinned ya again.

323
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:30,567
This is it. We made it.

324
00:18:34,821 --> 00:18:36,365
Whoa!

325
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:40,786
NALA: It's really creepy.

326
00:18:40,869 --> 00:18:41,954
Yeah.

327
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:43,288
Isn't it great?

328
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:46,500
- We could get in big trouble.
- I know!

329
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:49,711
I wonder if its brains are still in there.

330
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,672
There's only one way to know.

331
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,548
Come on, let's go check it out.

332
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:57,302
Wrong! The only checking out you
will do will be to check out of here.

333
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,637
Oh, man!

334
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:01,181
We're way beyond the boundary
of the Pride Lands.

335
00:19:01,348 --> 00:19:02,891
Look, banana beak is scared.

336
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,769
It's Mr. banana beak to you, fuzzy,

337
00:19:05,852 --> 00:19:09,272
and right now we are all
in very real danger.

338
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,774
Danger? Ha!

339
00:19:10,857 --> 00:19:12,901
I walk on the wild side.

340
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:15,237
I laugh in the face of danger.

341
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:16,780
Ha ha ha ha!

342
00:19:16,863 --> 00:19:18,240
(CACKLING)

343
00:19:24,162 --> 00:19:27,374
Well, well, well, Banzai,
what have we got here?

344
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:29,376
I don't know, Shenzi.

345
00:19:30,168 --> 00:19:31,795
What do you think, Ed?

346
00:19:31,878 --> 00:19:33,338
(CRAZY LAUGHTER)

347
00:19:34,047 --> 00:19:35,841
Just what I was thinking.

348
00:19:36,383 --> 00:19:37,884
A trio of trespassers!

349
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,220
And quite by accident,
let me assure you.

350
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:42,139
A simple navigational error.

351
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:44,182
Whoa, whoa, wait, wait, wait.

352
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:48,228
I know you.
You're Mufasa's little stooge.

353
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:50,647
I, madam, am the king's major-domo.

354
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:52,315
And that would make you...

355
00:19:52,399 --> 00:19:53,692
The future king.

356
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:57,404
Do you know what we do to kings
who step out of their kingdom?

357
00:19:57,571 --> 00:20:00,198
Huh! You can't do anything to me.

358
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:02,534
Technically, they can.
We are on their land.

359
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:06,830
But you told me they're nothing but
slobbering, mangy, stupid poachers.

360
00:20:06,913 --> 00:20:08,415
Ix-nay on the upid-stay.

361
00:20:08,582 --> 00:20:11,668
- Who are you callin' upid-stay?
- My, my, my. Oh, look at the sun!

362
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,920
- It's time to go!
- What's the hurry?

363
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,839
We'd love you to
stick around for dinner.

364
00:20:15,922 --> 00:20:19,342
Yeah, we could have
whatever's lion around!

365
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:21,344
Wait, wait, wait, I got one, I got one!

366
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:24,556
Make mine a cub sandwich!
Whaddaya think?

367
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:28,727
What, Ed? What is it?

368
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:30,604
Hey, did we order this dinner to go?

369
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:31,772
No, why?

370
00:20:31,938 --> 00:20:34,066
'Cause there it goes!

371
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:35,734
(PANTING)

372
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:38,570
(SQUAWKS)

373
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,991
- Did we lose 'em?
- I think so.

374
00:20:43,116 --> 00:20:44,493
Where's Zazu?

375
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:46,745
The little major-domo bird
hippety-hopped

376
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:48,830
all the way to the birdie-boiler.

377
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:51,958
Oh, no! Not the birdie-boiler!

378
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:54,002
Aaaah!

379
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:58,632
Hey, why don't you pick
on somebody your own size?

380
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:01,134
- Like you?
- Oops.

381
00:21:03,011 --> 00:21:05,305
Boo!

382
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:19,277
NALA: Simba!

383
00:21:22,989 --> 00:21:25,367
(SNARLS)

384
00:21:37,337 --> 00:21:40,799
Here, kitty, kitty, kitty.

385
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:43,885
(WEAK ROAR)

386
00:21:45,303 --> 00:21:46,680
That was it?

387
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:49,015
Do it again. Come on.

388
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:51,685
(DEEP ROAR)

389
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:54,855
(ROARING)

390
00:22:01,027 --> 00:22:03,530
- Oh, please, please! Uncle, uncle!
- Silence!

391
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,825
- We're gonna shut up right now!
- Calm down. We're really sorry.

392
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:10,036
If you ever come near my son again...

393
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:11,746
Oh, this is... This is your son?

394
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:14,374
- Oh, your son.
- Did you know that?

395
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:16,877
No. Me? I didn't know... No, did you?

396
00:22:16,918 --> 00:22:18,837
- No, of course not.
- No.

397
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,005
Ed?

398
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:22,757
(ROARS)

399
00:22:23,341 --> 00:22:24,676
Toodles.

400
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,686
- Dad, I...
- You deliberately disobeyed me.

401
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:38,940
- Dad, I'm... I'm sorry.
- Let's go home.

402
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:44,571
I thought you were very brave.

403
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:02,797
MUFASA: Zazu.

404
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:06,092
Yes, sire?

405
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:10,430
Take Nala home.
I've got to teach my son a lesson.

406
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:16,561
Come, Nala.

407
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:20,065
Simba, good luck.

408
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:27,739
Simba!

409
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,310
Simba, I'm very disappointed in you.

410
00:23:57,352 --> 00:23:59,813
- I know.
- You could've been killed.

411
00:23:59,854 --> 00:24:01,815
You deliberately disobeyed me,

412
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:05,652
and what's worse,
you put Nala in danger.

413
00:24:06,152 --> 00:24:08,321
I was just trying to be brave, like you.

414
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:11,825
I'm only brave when I have to be.

415
00:24:11,866 --> 00:24:15,495
Simba, being brave

416
00:24:15,578 --> 00:24:17,914
doesn't mean you go looking for trouble.

417
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:20,041
But you're not scared of anything.

418
00:24:21,209 --> 00:24:22,335
I was today.

419
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:24,587
- You were?
- Yes.

420
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,840
I thought I might lose you.

421
00:24:26,881 --> 00:24:30,885
I guess even kings get scared, huh?

422
00:24:31,011 --> 00:24:32,178
Mm-hmm.

423
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:34,514
- But you know what?
- What?

424
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:37,100
I think those hyenas
were even scareder.

425
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,560
(LAUGHS)

426
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:41,855
'Cause nobody messes with your dad.

427
00:24:41,938 --> 00:24:44,399
- Come here, you.
- Oh, no! No!

428
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:46,860
- Aagh! Uhh!
- (MUFASA CHUCKLES)

429
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:49,112
SIMBA: Come here!

430
00:24:49,195 --> 00:24:50,405
(BOTH LAUGH)

431
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:51,698
Gotcha!

432
00:24:55,535 --> 00:24:56,870
(PANTING)

433
00:24:56,911 --> 00:24:58,455
- Dad?
- Hmm?

434
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:01,291
- We're pals, right?
- Right.

435
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:04,127
And we'll always be together, right?

436
00:25:05,420 --> 00:25:11,134
Simba, let me tell you something
that my father told me.

437
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:13,136
Look at the stars.

438
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:18,308
The great kings of the past
look down on us from those stars.

439
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,727
- Really?
- Yes.

440
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,063
So whenever you feel alone,

441
00:25:23,146 --> 00:25:27,901
just remember that those kings
will always be there to guide you.

442
00:25:29,402 --> 00:25:31,237
And so will I.

443
00:25:37,994 --> 00:25:41,623
BANZAI: Man, that lousy Mufasa.
I won't be able to sit for a week.

444
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:43,083
(ED LAUGHS)

445
00:25:44,834 --> 00:25:46,461
It's not funny, Ed.

446
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,089
(LAUGHS HYSTERICALLY)

447
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:52,467
Hey, shut up!

448
00:25:52,592 --> 00:25:53,802
(SNARLS)

449
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:56,930
Will you knock it off?

450
00:25:58,139 --> 00:26:01,142
- Well, he started it.
- SHENZI: Look at you guys.

451
00:26:01,434 --> 00:26:03,812
No wonder we're dangling
at the bottom of the food chain.

452
00:26:03,937 --> 00:26:05,438
Man, I hate dangling.

453
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:09,317
Yeah? If it weren't for those lions,
we'd be runnin' the joint.

454
00:26:09,442 --> 00:26:10,819
Man, I hate lions.

455
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:12,612
- So pushy.
- And hairy.

456
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:14,781
- And stinky.
- And, man, are they...

457
00:26:14,823 --> 00:26:16,825
BOTH: Ugly!

458
00:26:18,284 --> 00:26:21,996
Oh, surely we lions are not all that bad.

459
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:24,958
- Oh.
- Oh, Scar. It's just you.

460
00:26:24,999 --> 00:26:27,127
We were afraid it was
somebody important.

461
00:26:27,168 --> 00:26:28,628
Yeah, you know, like Mufasa.

462
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:30,213
- SHENZI: Yeah.
- I see.

463
00:26:30,296 --> 00:26:32,632
- Now that's power!
- Tell me about it.

464
00:26:32,674 --> 00:26:34,467
I just hear that name and I shudder.

465
00:26:34,509 --> 00:26:37,137
- Mufasa!
- Ooh! Do it again.

466
00:26:37,178 --> 00:26:38,513
- Mufasa!
- Ooooh!

467
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:41,182
Mufasa! Mufasa! Mufasa!

468
00:26:41,891 --> 00:26:43,059
SHENZI: Ooh, it tingles me.

469
00:26:43,143 --> 00:26:46,020
I'm surrounded by idiots.

470
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:49,190
Now, you, Scar, I mean, you're
one of us. I mean, you're our pal.

471
00:26:49,315 --> 00:26:50,483
Charmed.

472
00:26:50,525 --> 00:26:54,654
Oh, I like that. He's not king,
but he's still so proper.

473
00:26:54,737 --> 00:26:56,656
Yeah. Hey, did you
bring us anything to eat,

474
00:26:56,698 --> 00:26:58,825
Scar, old buddy, old pal?
Huh? Did ya, did ya, did ya?

475
00:26:58,867 --> 00:27:01,202
I don't think you really deserve this.

476
00:27:01,327 --> 00:27:04,372
I practically gift-wrapped
those cubs for you,

477
00:27:04,497 --> 00:27:07,876
and you couldn't even dispose of them.

478
00:27:10,545 --> 00:27:14,674
Well, you know, it wasn't exactly
like they was alone, Scar.

479
00:27:14,716 --> 00:27:16,885
Yeah. What were we supposed to do?

480
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:18,887
(GULP) Kill Mufasa?

481
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:20,555
(CHEWING)

482
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,515
Precisely.

483
00:27:33,026 --> 00:27:36,905
(SINGING) <i>I know that your powers</i>
<i>of retention</i>

484
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:40,742
<i>Are as wet as a warthog's backside</i>

485
00:27:40,867 --> 00:27:45,038
<i>But thick as you are, pay attention</i>

486
00:27:45,079 --> 00:27:48,833
<i>My words are a matter of pride</i>

487
00:27:48,917 --> 00:27:52,587
<i>It's clear from your vacant expressions</i>

488
00:27:52,712 --> 00:27:56,591
<i>The lights are not all on upstairs</i>

489
00:27:56,716 --> 00:28:00,094
<i>But we're talking kings
and successions</i>

490
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:02,931
<i>Even you can't be caught unawares</i>

491
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:07,936
<i>So prepare for the chance of a lifetime</i>

492
00:28:08,019 --> 00:28:12,398
<i>Be prepared for sensational news</i>

493
00:28:12,482 --> 00:28:16,319
<i>A shiny new era is tiptoeing nearer</i>

494
00:28:16,402 --> 00:28:17,987
<i>And where do we feature?</i>

495
00:28:18,071 --> 00:28:20,281
<i>Just listen to teacher</i>

496
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:22,242
<i>I know it sounds sordid</i>

497
00:28:22,325 --> 00:28:24,202
<i>But you'll be rewarded</i>

498
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:27,830
<i>When at last I am given my dues</i>

499
00:28:27,914 --> 00:28:31,459
<i>And injustice deliciously squared</i>

500
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:34,754
<i>Be prepared</i>

501
00:28:34,837 --> 00:28:38,925
Yeah, be prepared.
We'll be prepared. For what?

502
00:28:39,008 --> 00:28:40,301
For the death of the king.

503
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:42,845
- Why, is he sick?
- No, fool, we're going to kill him.

504
00:28:42,929 --> 00:28:46,266
- And Simba, too.
- Great idea. Who needs a king?

505
00:28:46,349 --> 00:28:49,143
(SINGING)
<i>No king, no king, la-la la-la la la</i>

506
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:52,230
- Idiots! There will be a king!
- Hey, but you said...

507
00:28:52,313 --> 00:28:54,315
I will be king!

508
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:56,109
Stick with me,

509
00:28:56,192 --> 00:29:00,113
and you'll never go hungry again.

510
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:02,532
- Yeah! All right!
- Long live the king!

511
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:06,035
Long live the king! Long live the king!

512
00:29:07,954 --> 00:29:11,207
<i>It's great that we'll soon be connected</i>

513
00:29:11,291 --> 00:29:15,545
<i>With a king who'll be all-time adored</i>

514
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:19,132
<i>Of course, quid pro quo
you're expected</i>

515
00:29:19,215 --> 00:29:23,219
<i>To take certain duties on board</i>

516
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:27,056
<i>The future is littered with prizes</i>

517
00:29:27,181 --> 00:29:31,561
<i>And though I'm the main addressee</i>

518
00:29:31,644 --> 00:29:34,981
<i>The point that I must emphasize is</i>

519
00:29:35,064 --> 00:29:37,984
<i>You won't get a sniff without me!</i>

520
00:29:38,901 --> 00:29:42,488
<i>So prepare for the coup of the century</i>

521
00:29:42,572 --> 00:29:46,909
<i>Be prepared for the murkiest scam</i>

522
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:48,661
<i>Meticulous planning</i>

523
00:29:48,745 --> 00:29:50,663
<i>Tenacity spanning</i>

524
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,832
<i>Decades of denial</i>

525
00:29:52,915 --> 00:29:56,586
<i>ls simply why I'll be king undisputed</i>

526
00:29:56,669 --> 00:29:58,588
<i>Respected, saluted</i>

527
00:29:58,713 --> 00:30:02,091
<i>And seen for the wonder I am</i>

528
00:30:02,216 --> 00:30:05,928
<i>Yes, my teeth and ambitions are bared</i>

529
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:09,265
<i>Be prepared</i>

530
00:30:10,433 --> 00:30:13,770
<i>Yes, our teeth and ambitions are bared</i>

531
00:30:13,853 --> 00:30:17,774
<i>Be prepared</i>

532
00:30:18,316 --> 00:30:20,610
(ALL CACKLE)

533
00:30:30,244 --> 00:30:34,707
SCAR: You wait here. Your father has
a marvelous surprise for you.

534
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:36,042
Ooh, what is it?

535
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:39,337
If I told you, it wouldn't be
a surprise now, would it?

536
00:30:39,629 --> 00:30:41,422
If you tell me,
I'll still act surprised.

537
00:30:41,798 --> 00:30:45,385
Ho ho ho! You are such a naughty boy.

538
00:30:45,468 --> 00:30:48,596
- Come on, Uncle Scar.
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

539
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:51,015
This is just for you and your daddy.

540
00:30:51,140 --> 00:30:55,770
You know, a sort of father-son thing.

541
00:30:55,853 --> 00:30:58,648
Well, I'd better go get him.

542
00:30:58,773 --> 00:31:00,566
- I'll go with you.
- No.

543
00:31:02,026 --> 00:31:05,780
No. Just stay on this rock.

544
00:31:05,863 --> 00:31:07,865
You wouldn't want to end up
in another mess

545
00:31:07,990 --> 00:31:09,659
like you did with the hyenas.

546
00:31:09,826 --> 00:31:13,663
- You know about that?
- Simba, everybody knows about that.

547
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:16,332
- Really?
- Oh, yes.

548
00:31:16,416 --> 00:31:20,128
Lucky daddy was there
to save you, eh?

549
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:22,922
Oh, and just between us,

550
00:31:23,005 --> 00:31:26,384
you might want to work on
that little roar of yours, hmm?

551
00:31:26,759 --> 00:31:28,428
Oh. Okay.

552
00:31:31,097 --> 00:31:34,684
Hey, Uncle Scar,
will I like this surprise?

553
00:31:35,059 --> 00:31:39,063
Simba, it's to die for.

554
00:32:00,334 --> 00:32:01,794
- (STOMACH RUMBLES)
- Shut up.

555
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:05,256
I can't help it. I'm so hungry.
I got to have a wildebeest.

556
00:32:05,381 --> 00:32:06,799
Stay put.

557
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:09,194
Can't I just pick off
one of the little sick ones?

558
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:13,139
No. We wait for the signal from Scar.

559
00:32:15,141 --> 00:32:18,728
There he is. Let's go.

560
00:32:19,187 --> 00:32:22,106
"Little roar." Puh!

561
00:32:24,442 --> 00:32:25,568
Rarr!

562
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:28,780
Rrrarr!

563
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:34,952
- Rarr!
- (ROAR ECHOES)

564
00:32:38,623 --> 00:32:40,666
(RUMBLING)

565
00:32:43,503 --> 00:32:44,921
(BIRDS CAW)

566
00:33:23,459 --> 00:33:25,419
Oh, look, sire, the herd is on the move.

567
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,839
- Odd.
- Mufasa, quick.

568
00:33:27,922 --> 00:33:29,841
Stampede in the gorge.

569
00:33:29,924 --> 00:33:32,593
- Simba's down there!
- Simba?

570
00:33:54,657 --> 00:33:56,117
Zazu, help me!

571
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:58,244
Your father is on the way! Hold on!

572
00:33:58,327 --> 00:33:59,495
Hurry!

573
00:34:02,957 --> 00:34:05,668
There! There on that tree!

574
00:34:05,751 --> 00:34:07,086
Hold on, Simba!

575
00:34:08,462 --> 00:34:09,964
Dad!

576
00:34:14,010 --> 00:34:16,053
ZAZU: Oh, Scar, this is awful!

577
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:18,347
What'll we do? What'll we do?

578
00:34:18,431 --> 00:34:21,100
I'll go back for help, that's what I'll do.

579
00:34:57,011 --> 00:34:58,095
Dad!

580
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:22,620
MUFASA: Scar!

581
00:35:23,329 --> 00:35:26,290
- SCAR: Brother.
- Brother, help me!

582
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:37,802
Long live the king.

583
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:45,977
No!

584
00:35:57,446 --> 00:35:58,698
(COUGHS)

585
00:35:58,823 --> 00:36:00,157
Dad!

586
00:36:11,377 --> 00:36:12,378
(RUSTLING)

587
00:36:12,503 --> 00:36:13,546
Dad?

588
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:52,543
Dad?

589
00:36:53,419 --> 00:36:56,255
Dad, come on.

590
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:59,216
You got to get up.

591
00:36:59,341 --> 00:37:01,343
Dad?

592
00:37:01,427 --> 00:37:03,345
We got to go home.

593
00:37:14,523 --> 00:37:16,025
Help! (ECHOES)

594
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:21,030
Somebody!

595
00:37:21,447 --> 00:37:22,948
Anybody.

596
00:37:24,617 --> 00:37:25,785
Help.

597
00:37:44,970 --> 00:37:46,388
(SNIFFLES)

598
00:37:56,816 --> 00:38:00,486
Simba. What have you done?

599
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:04,740
There were wildebeests,
and he tried to save me.

600
00:38:05,241 --> 00:38:07,993
It was an accident.
I didn't mean for it to happen.

601
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:12,331
Of course. Of course you didn't.

602
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:17,837
No one ever means for
these things to happen.

603
00:38:18,003 --> 00:38:20,005
But the king is dead.

604
00:38:21,632 --> 00:38:24,635
And if it weren't for you,
he'd still be alive.

605
00:38:29,515 --> 00:38:31,976
Oh, what will your mother think?

606
00:38:32,309 --> 00:38:34,520
(SNIFFLES) What am I going to do?

607
00:38:34,645 --> 00:38:35,980
Run away, Simba.

608
00:38:37,314 --> 00:38:42,361
Run. Run away and never return.

609
00:38:49,118 --> 00:38:50,494
Kill him.

610
00:39:02,882 --> 00:39:04,008
(SNARLS)

611
00:39:27,907 --> 00:39:29,658
Whoa!

612
00:39:35,372 --> 00:39:37,499
- Yow!
- (LAUGHING)

613
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:40,169
Aah! Ohh! Yeow!

614
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:45,591
Hey, there he goes. There he goes.

615
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:47,259
So go get him.

616
00:39:47,384 --> 00:39:49,220
There ain't no way I'm going in there.

617
00:39:49,261 --> 00:39:53,182
What, you want me to come out
looking like you, cactus butt?

618
00:39:54,266 --> 00:39:55,601
But we got to finish the job.

619
00:39:55,684 --> 00:39:58,729
Well, he's as good as
dead out there anyway.

620
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:01,065
And if he comes back, we'll kill him.

621
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:03,234
Yeah! You hear that?

622
00:40:04,026 --> 00:40:07,279
If you ever come back, we'll kill you!

623
00:40:07,363 --> 00:40:08,697
(LAUGHING)

624
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:19,750
Mufasa's death is a terrible tragedy.

625
00:40:20,417 --> 00:40:24,213
But to lose Simba,
who had barely begun to live...

626
00:40:25,214 --> 00:40:30,052
For me, it is a deep, personal loss.

627
00:40:30,135 --> 00:40:34,098
So it is with a heavy heart
that I assume the throne.

628
00:40:34,139 --> 00:40:38,435
Yet out of the ashes of this tragedy
we shall rise

629
00:40:38,477 --> 00:40:41,480
to greet the dawning of a new era

630
00:40:41,563 --> 00:40:45,317
in which lion and hyena come together

631
00:40:45,442 --> 00:40:49,738
in a great and glorious future.

632
00:40:50,447 --> 00:40:52,658
(HYENAS WHOOP)

633
00:40:54,827 --> 00:40:56,120
(SIGHS)

634
00:41:20,769 --> 00:41:22,646
(CAWING)

635
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:34,325
Yaaaah!

636
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:39,204
Get out! Get out! Get out of here!

637
00:41:39,288 --> 00:41:41,623
I love this! Bowling for buzzards.

638
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:45,294
Hee hee hee! Gets 'em every time.

639
00:41:45,502 --> 00:41:49,381
Uh-oh.
Hey, Timon, you better come look.

640
00:41:49,506 --> 00:41:51,550
I think it's still alive.

641
00:41:51,717 --> 00:41:52,885
Eeeuw.

642
00:41:53,218 --> 00:41:56,388
All righty, what have we got here?

643
00:41:56,513 --> 00:41:57,723
(SNIFFS)

644
00:42:00,893 --> 00:42:02,227
(GRUNTS)

645
00:42:02,311 --> 00:42:05,564
Jeez, it's a lion! Run, Pumbaa, move it!

646
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:09,026
Hey, Timon, it's just a little lion.

647
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:13,697
Look at him. He's so cute and all alone.

648
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:16,200
- Can we keep him?
- Pumbaa, are you nuts?

649
00:42:16,283 --> 00:42:19,536
You're talking about a lion.
Lions eat guys like us.

650
00:42:19,620 --> 00:42:22,081
- But he's so little.
- He's going to get bigger.

651
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:24,333
Maybe he'll be on our side.

652
00:42:24,416 --> 00:42:27,461
That's the stupidest thing
I ever heard. Maybe he'll...

653
00:42:27,544 --> 00:42:30,839
Hey, I've got it.
What if he's on our side?

654
00:42:30,923 --> 00:42:34,218
You know, having a lion around
might not be such a bad idea.

655
00:42:34,301 --> 00:42:35,386
So we're keeping him?

656
00:42:35,469 --> 00:42:37,721
Of course.
Who's the brains of this outfit?

657
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:39,431
- Uh...
- My point exactly.

658
00:42:39,556 --> 00:42:42,810
Jeez, I'm fried. Let's get out
of here and find some shade.

659
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:53,612
- You okay, kid?
- I guess so.

660
00:42:53,737 --> 00:42:54,947
You nearly died.

661
00:42:55,072 --> 00:42:56,657
- I saved you.
- (SNORTS)

662
00:42:56,782 --> 00:42:58,909
Well, Pumbaa helped. A little.

663
00:42:58,992 --> 00:43:00,828
Thanks for your help.

664
00:43:01,995 --> 00:43:03,288
Hey, where you going?

665
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:05,582
Nowhere.

666
00:43:05,666 --> 00:43:07,000
Gee, he looks blue.

667
00:43:07,126 --> 00:43:11,380
- I'd say brownish gold.
- No, no, no. I mean he's depressed.

668
00:43:13,048 --> 00:43:14,091
Kid, what's eating you?

669
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:17,261
Nothing.
He's at the top of the food chain.

670
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:21,140
The food chain!

671
00:43:23,016 --> 00:43:24,143
Ahem.

672
00:43:25,310 --> 00:43:26,728
So, where you from?

673
00:43:26,812 --> 00:43:28,814
Who cares? I can't go back.

674
00:43:29,022 --> 00:43:32,317
Ah, you're an outcast.
That's great. So are we.

675
00:43:32,401 --> 00:43:34,778
- What'd you do, kid?
- Something terrible.

676
00:43:34,862 --> 00:43:37,865
- But I don't want to talk about it.
- We don't want to hear about it.

677
00:43:37,990 --> 00:43:40,159
Come on, Timon. Anything we can do?

678
00:43:40,242 --> 00:43:42,870
Not unless you can change the past.

679
00:43:42,995 --> 00:43:46,248
You know, kid, in times like this,
my buddy Timon here says,

680
00:43:46,331 --> 00:43:48,834
"You got to put your
behind in your past."

681
00:43:48,917 --> 00:43:50,502
No, no, no.

682
00:43:50,586 --> 00:43:51,920
- I mean...
- Amateur.

683
00:43:52,004 --> 00:43:54,173
Lie down before you hurt yourself.

684
00:43:54,673 --> 00:43:57,384
It's,
"You got to put your past behind you."

685
00:43:57,468 --> 00:44:01,472
Look, kid, bad things happen, and you
can't do anything about it, right?

686
00:44:01,555 --> 00:44:02,598
- Right.
- Wrong!

687
00:44:02,681 --> 00:44:05,309
When the world turns its back on you,

688
00:44:05,392 --> 00:44:08,103
you turn your back on the world.

689
00:44:08,187 --> 00:44:10,063
Well, that's not what I was taught.

690
00:44:10,189 --> 00:44:12,357
Then maybe you need a new lesson.

691
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:14,776
Repeat after me. Ahem.

692
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:16,653
<i>- Hakuna matata.</i>
- What?

693
00:44:17,112 --> 00:44:19,698
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

694
00:44:19,781 --> 00:44:20,991
It means "no worries".

695
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:24,036
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

696
00:44:24,119 --> 00:44:27,289
What a wonderful phrase.

697
00:44:27,372 --> 00:44:29,708
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

698
00:44:29,791 --> 00:44:33,045
(SINGING) <i>Ain't no passing craze</i>

699
00:44:33,128 --> 00:44:35,464
<i>It means no worries</i>

700
00:44:35,547 --> 00:44:39,635
<i>For the rest of your days</i>

701
00:44:39,718 --> 00:44:44,723
<i>It's our problem-free philosophy</i>

702
00:44:44,806 --> 00:44:47,309
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

703
00:44:47,392 --> 00:44:49,144
<i>Hakuna matata?</i>

704
00:44:49,228 --> 00:44:51,813
- Yeah. It's our motto.
- What's a motto?

705
00:44:51,897 --> 00:44:54,191
Nothin'. What's-a-motto with you?

706
00:44:55,317 --> 00:44:59,154
You know, kid, these two words
will solve all your problems.

707
00:44:59,238 --> 00:45:02,574
That's right.
Take Pumbaa, for example. Why...

708
00:45:02,658 --> 00:45:05,410
(SINGING) <i>When he was</i>
<i>a young warthog</i>

709
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:09,331
<i>When I was a young warthog</i>

710
00:45:09,414 --> 00:45:11,250
- Very nice.
- Thanks.

711
00:45:11,667 --> 00:45:14,253
<i>He found his aroma
lacked a certain appeal</i>

712
00:45:14,336 --> 00:45:16,588
<i>He could clear the savanna
after every meal</i>

713
00:45:16,672 --> 00:45:18,757
<i>I'm a sensitive soul</i>

714
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:21,343
<i>Though I seem thick-skinned</i>

715
00:45:21,426 --> 00:45:22,511
(BREAKS WIND)

716
00:45:22,594 --> 00:45:27,724
<i>And it hurt that my friends
never stood downwind</i>

717
00:45:27,808 --> 00:45:31,395
<i>- And, oh, the shame
- He was ashamed</i>

718
00:45:31,478 --> 00:45:33,939
<i>- Thought of changing my name
- Oh, what's in a name?</i>

719
00:45:34,022 --> 00:45:35,566
<i>And I got downhearted</i>

720
00:45:35,649 --> 00:45:37,609
<i>- How did you feel?
- Every time that I...</i>

721
00:45:37,693 --> 00:45:40,445
- Hey, not in front of the kids.
- Oh, sorry.

722
00:45:41,363 --> 00:45:43,448
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

723
00:45:43,532 --> 00:45:46,785
<i>What a wonderful phrase</i>

724
00:45:46,868 --> 00:45:48,662
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

725
00:45:48,787 --> 00:45:51,957
<i>Ain't no passing craze</i>

726
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:54,251
<i>It means no worries</i>

727
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:56,211
<i>For the rest of your days</i>

728
00:45:56,295 --> 00:45:57,963
Yeah, sing it, kid.

729
00:45:58,046 --> 00:46:00,966
<i>It's our problem-free</i>

730
00:46:01,550 --> 00:46:03,677
<i>Philosophy</i>

731
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:07,055
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

732
00:46:07,806 --> 00:46:09,725
Welcome to our humble home.

733
00:46:09,808 --> 00:46:12,394
- You live here?
- We live wherever we want.

734
00:46:12,477 --> 00:46:14,896
Yep. Home is where your rump rests.

735
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:16,732
It's beautiful.

736
00:46:17,107 --> 00:46:18,942
(BELCHES) I'm starved.

737
00:46:19,026 --> 00:46:21,320
I'm so hungry I could eat a whole zebra.

738
00:46:21,945 --> 00:46:24,114
Ah. We're fresh out of zebra.

739
00:46:24,197 --> 00:46:25,907
- Any antelope?
- Nuh-uh.

740
00:46:25,991 --> 00:46:27,576
- Hippo?
- Nope.

741
00:46:27,659 --> 00:46:30,787
Listen, kid, if you live with us,
you have to eat like us.

742
00:46:30,871 --> 00:46:33,415
Hey, this looks like a good spot
to rustle up some grub.

743
00:46:34,666 --> 00:46:36,001
Eugh, what's that?

744
00:46:36,084 --> 00:46:37,878
A grub. What's it look like?

745
00:46:37,961 --> 00:46:39,921
Eugh! Gross.

746
00:46:40,172 --> 00:46:42,507
Mmm. Tastes like chicken.

747
00:46:43,675 --> 00:46:46,303
Slimy yet satisfying.

