01:01:40,905 --> 01:01:43,407
No, no, no. It doesn't matter.
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

992
01:01:43,574 --> 01:01:45,243
- What?
<i>- Hakuna matata.</i>

993
01:01:45,409 --> 01:01:48,955
It's something I learned out here.
Sometimes bad things happen...

994
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:50,122
Simba...

995
01:01:50,248 --> 01:01:53,459
...and there's nothing you can do
about it. So why worry?

996
01:01:53,584 --> 01:01:58,089
- Because it's your responsibility.
- Well, what about you? You left.

997
01:01:58,214 --> 01:02:01,050
I left to find help, and I found you.

998
01:02:01,259 --> 01:02:05,555
Don't you understand?
You're our only hope.

999
01:02:05,596 --> 01:02:08,432
- Sorry.
- What's happened to you?

1000
01:02:08,933 --> 01:02:12,478
- You're not the Simba I remember.
- You're right. I'm not.

1001
01:02:12,603 --> 01:02:16,148
- Now are you satisfied?
- No. Just disappointed.

1002
01:02:16,274 --> 01:02:19,068
You know, you're starting
to sound like my father.

1003
01:02:19,110 --> 01:02:21,112
Good. At least one of us does.

1004
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:25,491
You think you can just show
up and tell me how to live my life?

1005
01:02:25,616 --> 01:02:27,618
You don't even know
what I've been through.

1006
01:02:27,660 --> 01:02:28,995
I would if you'd just tell me.

1007
01:02:29,120 --> 01:02:30,955
- Forget it!
- Fine!

1008
01:02:34,792 --> 01:02:37,628
She's wrong. I can't go back.

1009
01:02:38,087 --> 01:02:41,799
What would it prove, anyway?
It won't change anything.

1010
01:02:42,008 --> 01:02:43,843
You can't change the past.

1011
01:02:47,013 --> 01:02:50,099
You said you'd always be there for me!

1012
01:02:50,641 --> 01:02:52,476
But you're not.

1013
01:02:54,604 --> 01:02:56,856
And it's because of me.

1014
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:59,984
It's my fault.

1015
01:03:00,192 --> 01:03:02,486
It's my fault.

1016
01:03:02,987 --> 01:03:04,614
(CRIES)

1017
01:03:06,157 --> 01:03:08,159
(SINGING) <i>Asante Sana,</i>
<i>squash banana</i>

1018
01:03:08,200 --> 01:03:09,535
<i>We we nugu, imi mi apana</i>

1019
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:11,454
<i>Asante Sana, squash banana</i>

1020
01:03:11,495 --> 01:03:13,205
<i>We we nugu, imi mi apana</i>

1021
01:03:13,331 --> 01:03:15,207
<i>Asante Sana, squash banana</i>

1022
01:03:15,333 --> 01:03:17,376
<i>We we nugu, imi mi apana</i>

1023
01:03:19,837 --> 01:03:21,672
(CHUCKLES)

1024
01:03:40,191 --> 01:03:41,400
(SIGHS)

1025
01:03:41,525 --> 01:03:45,404
<i>Asante Sana, squash banana
We we nugu, imi mi apana</i>

1026
01:03:47,073 --> 01:03:48,699
Come on, will you cut it out?

1027
01:03:48,866 --> 01:03:51,702
Can't cut it out. It'll grow right back!
(LAUGHS)

1028
01:03:51,869 --> 01:03:54,872
Creepy little monkey.
Will you stop following me?

1029
01:03:55,039 --> 01:03:58,876
- Who are you?
- The question is, who are you?

1030
01:04:01,879 --> 01:04:05,049
I thought I knew. Now I'm not so sure.

1031
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:08,928
Well, I know who you are.
Shh. Come here. It's a secret.

1032
01:04:09,053 --> 01:04:12,431
<i>Asante Sana, squash banana</i>

1033
01:04:12,556 --> 01:04:14,934
Grrr! Enough!
What is that supposed to mean?

1034
01:04:15,059 --> 01:04:18,396
It means you are a baboon, and I'm not.

1035
01:04:20,064 --> 01:04:22,274
I think you're a little confused.

1036
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:25,236
Wrong! I'm not the one who's confused.

1037
01:04:25,403 --> 01:04:28,781
- You don't even know who you are.
- Oh, and I suppose you know.

1038
01:04:28,906 --> 01:04:31,909
Sure do. You're Mufasa's boy.

1039
01:04:33,411 --> 01:04:36,080
- Bye.
- Hey, wait!

1040
01:04:45,089 --> 01:04:46,090
You knew my father?

1041
01:04:46,215 --> 01:04:49,427
Correction, I know your father.

1042
01:04:51,637 --> 01:04:53,472
I hate to tell you this,

1043
01:04:53,597 --> 01:04:56,642
but he died a long time ago.

1044
01:04:56,767 --> 01:04:58,894
Nope. Wrong again!

1045
01:04:58,936 --> 01:05:00,271
Ha ha ha!

1046
01:05:00,438 --> 01:05:03,149
He's alive, and I'll show him to you.

1047
01:05:03,274 --> 01:05:06,277
You follow old Rafiki.
He knows the way. Come on!

1048
01:05:16,162 --> 01:05:18,330
Don't dawdle. Hurry up!

1049
01:05:18,456 --> 01:05:21,917
- Hey, whoa, wait, wait.
- Come on. Come on!

1050
01:05:23,627 --> 01:05:25,796
Would you slow down?

1051
01:05:26,672 --> 01:05:28,758
(RAFIKI LAUGHS)

1052
01:05:36,974 --> 01:05:39,143
Stop!

1053
01:05:43,981 --> 01:05:45,483
(WHISPERS) Look down there.

1054
01:06:10,674 --> 01:06:13,636
That's not my father.
That's just my reflection.

1055
01:06:13,677 --> 01:06:15,346
No.

1056
01:06:16,514 --> 01:06:19,350
Look harder.

1057
01:06:25,523 --> 01:06:26,857
You see?

1058
01:06:28,192 --> 01:06:30,694
He lives in you.

1059
01:06:34,865 --> 01:06:37,535
MUFASA: Simba.

1060
01:06:37,576 --> 01:06:39,203
Father?

1061
01:06:47,169 --> 01:06:49,880
Simba, you have forgotten me.

1062
01:06:50,047 --> 01:06:52,091
No. How could I?

1063
01:06:52,216 --> 01:06:56,929
You have forgotten who you are,
and so have forgotten me.

1064
01:06:57,054 --> 01:06:59,265
Look inside yourself, Simba.

1065
01:06:59,723 --> 01:07:03,435
You are more than
what you have become.

1066
01:07:03,561 --> 01:07:06,897
You must take your place
in the circle of life.

1067
01:07:06,939 --> 01:07:10,901
How can I go back?
I'm not who I used to be.

1068
01:07:11,068 --> 01:07:14,905
Remember who you are.

1069
01:07:14,947 --> 01:07:18,909
You are my son and the one true king.

1070
01:07:20,744 --> 01:07:24,415
Remember who you are.

1071
01:07:24,456 --> 01:07:27,293
No! Please, don't leave me!

1072
01:07:27,418 --> 01:07:28,586
MUFASA: Remember.

1073
01:07:28,627 --> 01:07:30,254
- Father!
- Remember!

1074
01:07:30,296 --> 01:07:32,256
Don't leave me.

1075
01:07:32,381 --> 01:07:34,258
Remember.

1076
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:44,935
What was that? Ha ha!

1077
01:07:44,977 --> 01:07:46,729
The weather. (SPLUTTERS)

1078
01:07:46,770 --> 01:07:50,441
- Very peculiar, don't you think?
- Yeah.

1079
01:07:51,066 --> 01:07:52,568
Looks like the winds are changing.

1080
01:07:52,610 --> 01:07:55,154
Ahh, change is good.

1081
01:07:55,613 --> 01:07:57,448
Yeah, but it's not easy.

1082
01:07:57,489 --> 01:08:02,494
I know what I have to do, but going
back means I'll have to face my past.

1083
01:08:03,621 --> 01:08:05,664
I've been running from it
for so long.

1084
01:08:06,624 --> 01:08:08,959
Ow! Jeez! What was that for?

1085
01:08:09,001 --> 01:08:11,921
It doesn't matter. It's in the past.

1086
01:08:11,962 --> 01:08:13,964
Yeah, but it still hurts.

1087
01:08:14,089 --> 01:08:16,342
Oh, yes, the past can hurt.

1088
01:08:16,467 --> 01:08:20,012
But the way I see it
you can either run from it

1089
01:08:20,137 --> 01:08:22,973
or learn from it.

1090
01:08:23,015 --> 01:08:25,809
Ah! You see?
So what are you going to do?

1091
01:08:26,018 --> 01:08:28,479
First, I'm gonna take your stick.

1092
01:08:28,604 --> 01:08:30,814
No, no, no, no! Not the stick!

1093
01:08:30,940 --> 01:08:34,485
- Hey! Where are you going?
- I'm going back!

1094
01:08:34,610 --> 01:08:37,488
Good! Go on! Get out of here!

1095
01:08:37,655 --> 01:08:38,989
(LAUGHS)

1096
01:08:40,157 --> 01:08:42,493
Whoo! Ha ha ha!

1097
01:08:42,534 --> 01:08:46,538
Whoooo! Whoooo!

1098
01:08:49,833 --> 01:08:51,335
(SNORES)

1099
01:08:54,380 --> 01:08:55,547
Grubs! Grubs!

1100
01:09:01,136 --> 01:09:03,055
Hey. Hey, wake up.

1101
01:09:07,059 --> 01:09:10,521
It's okay! Whoa, whoa!
It's okay! It's me!

1102
01:09:11,563 --> 01:09:14,024
Don't ever do that again.

1103
01:09:14,358 --> 01:09:16,026
Carnivores! Oy!

1104
01:09:16,151 --> 01:09:18,737
- Have you guys seen Simba?
- I thought he was with you.

1105
01:09:18,862 --> 01:09:21,532
He was, but now I can't find him.
Where is he?

1106
01:09:21,573 --> 01:09:23,534
Ho ho! You won't find him here!

1107
01:09:23,867 --> 01:09:26,996
Ha ha! The king has returned.

1108
01:09:27,079 --> 01:09:30,249
I can't believe it. He's gone back!

1109
01:09:30,374 --> 01:09:32,209
Gone back? What do you mean?

1110
01:09:32,376 --> 01:09:35,254
Hey, what's goin' on here?

1111
01:09:35,379 --> 01:09:37,715
- Who's the monkey?
- Simba went back to challenge Scar.

1112
01:09:37,756 --> 01:09:38,882
- Who?
- Scar.

1113
01:09:38,924 --> 01:09:40,759
- Who's got a scar?
- No, it's his uncle.

1114
01:09:40,884 --> 01:09:42,594
- The monkey's his uncle?
- No!

1115
01:09:42,720 --> 01:09:46,265
Simba's gone back to challenge
his uncle to take his place as king.

1116
01:09:46,390 --> 01:09:47,683
BOTH: Oh.

1117
01:10:44,948 --> 01:10:46,950
NALA: Simba, wait up!

1118
01:10:50,496 --> 01:10:54,792
- It's awful, isn't it?
- I didn't want to believe you.

1119
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,794
What made you come back?

1120
01:10:57,294 --> 01:10:59,797
I finally got some sense
knocked into me,

1121
01:11:00,130 --> 01:11:02,132
and I've got the bump to prove it.

1122
01:11:02,508 --> 01:11:04,968
Besides, this is my kingdom.

1123
01:11:05,302 --> 01:11:08,097
If I don't fight for it, who will?

1124
01:11:08,347 --> 01:11:11,141
- I will.
- It's gonna be dangerous.

1125
01:11:11,266 --> 01:11:15,687
Danger? Ha!
I laugh in the face of danger. Ha ha ha!

1126
01:11:15,813 --> 01:11:17,523
I see nothing funny about this.

1127
01:11:17,648 --> 01:11:20,651
Timon! Pumbaa!
What are you doing here?

1128
01:11:20,776 --> 01:11:22,861
At your service, my liege.

1129
01:11:22,986 --> 01:11:26,657
Aww! We're gonna fight your uncle
for this?

1130
01:11:27,116 --> 01:11:30,369
Yes, Timon. This is my home.

1131
01:11:30,494 --> 01:11:32,830
Oh. Talk about your fixer-upper!

1132
01:11:33,163 --> 01:11:37,376
Well, Simba, if it's important to
you, we're with you to the end.

1133
01:11:56,186 --> 01:12:00,023
Hyenas. I hate hyenas.

1134
01:12:00,149 --> 01:12:02,568
So what's your plan
for getting past those guys?

1135
01:12:02,985 --> 01:12:06,029
- Live bait.
- Good idea. Hey!

1136
01:12:06,155 --> 01:12:08,907
Come on, Timon. You guys
have to create a diversion.

1137
01:12:09,199 --> 01:12:11,660
What do you want me to do,
dress in drag and do the hula?

1138
01:12:11,869 --> 01:12:13,829
- (DRUMS)
- Luau!

1139
01:12:13,871 --> 01:12:15,682
(SINGING) <i>If you're hungry for a hunk</i>
<i>of fat and juicy meat</i>

1140
01:12:15,706 --> 01:12:17,506
<i>Eat my buddy Pumbaa here
because he is a treat</i>

1141
01:12:17,541 --> 01:12:19,501
<i>Come on down and dine
on this tasty swine</i>

1142
01:12:19,543 --> 01:12:21,545
<i>All you have to do is get in line</i>

1143
01:12:21,712 --> 01:12:23,505
<i>- Are you achin'</i>
- Yep, yep, yep.

1144
01:12:23,547 --> 01:12:25,424
<i>- For some bacon?</i>
- Yep, yep, yep.

1145
01:12:25,549 --> 01:12:27,092
<i>- He's a big pig</i>
- Yep, yep.

1146
01:12:27,217 --> 01:12:29,261
<i>You could be a big pig, too! Oi!</i>

1147
01:12:34,266 --> 01:12:37,603
Nala, you find my mother
and rally the lionesses.

1148
01:12:37,728 --> 01:12:40,606
I'll look for Scar.

1149
01:12:41,565 --> 01:12:42,858
(THUNDER)

1150
01:12:43,066 --> 01:12:44,735
Sarabi!

1151
01:12:55,954 --> 01:12:57,247
(THUNDER)

1152
01:12:59,416 --> 01:13:00,626
Yes, Scar?

1153
01:13:00,751 --> 01:13:04,213
Where is your hunting party?
They're not doing their job.

1154
01:13:04,254 --> 01:13:07,132
Scar, there is no food.
The herds have moved on.

1155
01:13:07,424 --> 01:13:09,927
No, you're just not
looking hard enough.

1156
01:13:09,968 --> 01:13:13,972
It's over. There is nothing left.

1157
01:13:14,097 --> 01:13:17,935
We have only one choice.
We must leave Pride Rock.

1158
01:13:18,101 --> 01:13:21,480
- We're not going anywhere.
- You have sentenced us to death.

1159
01:13:21,605 --> 01:13:23,774
- Then so be it.
- You can't do that.

1160
01:13:23,815 --> 01:13:26,109
I am the king. I can do whatever I want.

1161
01:13:26,235 --> 01:13:28,612
If you were half the king Mufasa was...

1162
01:13:28,737 --> 01:13:31,281
I'm ten times the king Mufasa was!

1163
01:13:31,949 --> 01:13:33,283
(ROARS)

1164
01:13:34,284 --> 01:13:36,745
Mufasa? No, you're dead.

1165
01:13:41,124 --> 01:13:42,459
(GROANS)

1166
01:13:44,002 --> 01:13:45,629
Mufasa?

1167
01:13:46,964 --> 01:13:49,091
No. It's me.

1168
01:13:49,800 --> 01:13:54,805
Simba! You're alive? How can that be?

1169
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:58,684
It doesn't matter. I'm home.

1170
01:13:58,809 --> 01:14:00,143
Simba?

1171
01:14:00,185 --> 01:14:04,815
Simba! Oh, I'm a little surprised
to see you

1172
01:14:04,856 --> 01:14:06,316
alive.

1173
01:14:07,985 --> 01:14:11,488
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't rip you apart.

1174
01:14:11,613 --> 01:14:13,532
Oh, Simba, you must understand.

1175
01:14:13,657 --> 01:14:15,993
The pressures of ruling a kingdom...

1176
01:14:16,118 --> 01:14:19,329
Are no longer yours. Step down, Scar.

1177
01:14:19,454 --> 01:14:21,832
Oh, well, I would, naturally.

1178
01:14:21,999 --> 01:14:24,876
However, there is one little problem.

1179
01:14:25,335 --> 01:14:26,795
You see them?

1180
01:14:28,505 --> 01:14:30,799
They think I'm king.

1181
01:14:30,841 --> 01:14:34,636
Well, we don't.
Simba's the rightful king.

1182
01:14:34,678 --> 01:14:36,638
The choice is yours, Scar.

1183
01:14:37,014 --> 01:14:39,182
Either step down or fight.

1184
01:14:39,308 --> 01:14:41,685
Oh, must this all end in violence?

1185
01:14:42,185 --> 01:14:46,023
I'd hate to be responsible
for the death of a family member.

1186
01:14:46,064 --> 01:14:49,359
- Wouldn't you agree, Simba?
- That's not gonna work, Scar.

1187
01:14:49,860 --> 01:14:50,986
I've put it behind me.

1188
01:14:51,028 --> 01:14:52,863
But what about your faithful subjects?

1189
01:14:52,988 --> 01:14:54,906
Have they put it behind them?

1190
01:14:55,032 --> 01:14:57,075
Simba, what is he talking about?

1191
01:14:57,200 --> 01:15:01,413
Ah, so you haven't told them
your little secret.

1192
01:15:01,538 --> 01:15:04,875
Well, Simba,
now's your chance to tell them.

1193
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:09,171
Tell them who is responsible
for Mufasa's death.

1194
01:15:12,215 --> 01:15:13,383
I am.

1195
01:15:17,721 --> 01:15:20,265
It's not true.

1196
01:15:20,724 --> 01:15:23,060
Tell me it's not true.

1197
01:15:24,561 --> 01:15:27,731
- It's true.
- You see? He admits it!

1198
01:15:27,856 --> 01:15:30,859
- Murderer!
- No! It was an accident.

1199
01:15:30,901 --> 01:15:34,613
If it weren't for you, Mufasa would
be alive. It's your fault he's dead!

1200
01:15:34,738 --> 01:15:36,281
- Do you deny it?
- No.

1201
01:15:36,406 --> 01:15:40,535
- Then you're guilty.
- No, I'm not a murderer!

1202
01:15:40,619 --> 01:15:42,913
Oh, Simba, you're in trouble again,

1203
01:15:43,080 --> 01:15:46,041
but this time
daddy isn't here to save you,

1204
01:15:46,083 --> 01:15:49,419
and now everyone knows why!

1205
01:15:50,462 --> 01:15:51,588
Simba!

1206
01:15:57,135 --> 01:15:59,971
Now, this looks familiar.

1207
01:16:00,389 --> 01:16:01,765
Hmm.

1208
01:16:01,807 --> 01:16:05,769
Where have I seen this before?
Let me think. Hmm.

1209
01:16:05,894 --> 01:16:08,480
Oh, yes. I remember.

1210
01:16:09,106 --> 01:16:12,776
This is just the way
your father looked before he died.

1211
01:16:14,611 --> 01:16:18,323
And here's my little secret.

1212
01:16:18,782 --> 01:16:21,952
(WHISPERING) I killed Mufasa.

1213
01:16:23,578 --> 01:16:26,623
No! Murderer!

1214
01:16:27,457 --> 01:16:29,918
- No, Simba, please.
- Tell them the truth.

1215
01:16:29,960 --> 01:16:33,672
Truth? But truth is in
the eye of the behold...

1216
01:16:34,131 --> 01:16:35,173
All right.

1217
01:16:35,632 --> 01:16:37,467
(GAGS) All right.

1218
01:16:38,510 --> 01:16:40,011
I did it.

1219
01:16:40,137 --> 01:16:42,013
So they can hear you.

1220
01:16:43,098 --> 01:16:46,268
I killed Mufasa!

1221
01:16:56,319 --> 01:16:58,321
Hee-yah!

1222
01:16:58,447 --> 01:17:01,658
Excuse me. Pardon me.
Comin' through. Hot stuff. Whoo!

1223
01:17:11,293 --> 01:17:12,669
(SCREECHES)

1224
01:17:16,840 --> 01:17:19,676
(NINJA FIGHTING NOISES)

1225
01:17:27,976 --> 01:17:29,478
Aagghh!

1226
01:17:30,979 --> 01:17:33,482
- Let me out! Let me out!
- Let me in! Let me in!

1227
01:17:34,691 --> 01:17:37,194
- (HYENA LAUGHS)
- Please, don't eat me.

1228
01:17:37,235 --> 01:17:38,862
Drop 'em!

1229
01:17:38,904 --> 01:17:41,239
- Hey, who's the pig?
- Are you talkin' to me?

1230
